    <item>
      <title>White Cross</title>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 May 2024 10:55:09 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://crazymilk.net/blog/white-cross.html</guid>
      <link>https://crazymilk.net/blog/white-cross.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
        <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/white-cross.webp" alt="View of a lake on a sunny day. Green pasture dotted with yellow flowers is in the foreground together with a park bench under a large white cross. The sky is cloudless and blue." width=960 height=540 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        <p>Hiked up to the White Cross (Weisses Kreuz) this morning for the first time in four and a half months. Fantastic views as always, especially for 40 minutes from my front door. I should do this hike more often (it's harder than my typical farm field walks and takes a bit more time).</p>
        <img src="https://crazymilk.net/files/images/photos/white-cross-2.webp" alt="View of light green pasture and dark green forested hills on a sunny day. A large white cross is silhouetted against a cloudless blue sky. A few snow-covered mountains are visible in the far distance." width=960 height=540 loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
      ]]></description>
    </item>

